			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I dropped this in the 12 page thread in general, but thought it could be better discussed here.
<br />

<br />
Rytan is on the right track by wanting to improve a variety of aspects of pets, but his proposed solutions do not go far enough. 
<br />

<br />
Its been said time and time again that a lot of our abilities encroach on other classes. Gaining a significant boost in one area will piss people off. 
<br />

<br />
The easiest existing ability to address would be magician healing. Up until now, the primary use for healing would be to keep the pet alive while a couple of mobs killed themselves on the DS. Too bad this doesn't really work well past level 50 or so. The complete inefficiency of our heal spells suggest that we should always prefer to burn a mob down as opposed to healing our pet. The problem is, the pet doesn't last long enough to burn the mob down. When offtanking or soloing in higher level zones, it is difficult to get off more than one nuke before the pet dies. If we nuke then heal, the heal doesn't provide enough hp to keep the pet alive for another nuke. We start chaining very inefficent heals, and spend far more mana than we can easily regenerate doing so. 
<br />

<br />
My suggestion within existing abilities would be the following: 
<br />

<br />
1) TER will heal a pet for 3000 hitpoints for 400 mana. With a 15% foci, the spell should cast in 5 seconds. 
<br />
2) Planar Renewal will heal a pet for 4000 hitpoints for 300 mana. the spell should cast in 4 seconds. 
<br />
3) The recast delay should be removed from these spells. This would allow the mage to keep the pet alive as long as their mana bar would support it. 
<br />

<br />
The mend companion AA should be designed to heal ~95% of the pet's health, with AA's to shorten the reuse and extend the capability into future expansions. Essentially a mana free heal that could be added in to the mix, if you wanted time to cast another nuke.
<br />

<br />
The RP Justification: If we can cast a pet for 400 mana, we should be able to renew most of that pet for a similar amount of mana. 
<br />

<br />
This, combined with some of the mitigation improvements that Rytan has suggested, might start helping magicians in an offtanking role. 
<br />

<br />
Would this be overpowered? I don't really think so. Our pets already underperform in DPS compared to when we nuke. The way things are currently balanced with pet heals, we're better off chaining a new pet, without equipment and buffs, which further lowers their DPS (not to mention the aggro reset that occurs as well). Making pet heals a viable replacement for chaining would not be overpowered, simply because the pets are underpowered to begin with. Being able to keep our pets alive cheaply would not encroach on anyone else's abilities. Also, if Time level mages get foci that dramatically increase pet hp and mitigation, perhaps an ancient pet healing spell could be added to compelement the foci. 
<br />

<br />
To extend our abilities a little further and add some more variety to the mix: 
<br />
A weapon with a low % slow would help this even further. One of the things that SOE could consider doing along with the additional weapon summons is to allow weapon delay to affect pets again. If we choose to give a pet a utility weapon like snare/slow, they would swing that weapon fewer times. We gain utility, but sacrifice pet DPS in the process.  
<br />

<br />
Its hard to say though, without seeing these kinds of ideas in action. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
PS. I didn't say it earlier, but I am grateful that they are extending some of these benefits innately within the pets. That is appreciated.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1002541&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
Arch Mage of 63 Seasons - <a href="http://www.stormhammer.org/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer</a>
