			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For me, heals have been a sore point. It seems reasonable to me that a mage should be able to heal full-bore against the DPS their pet would take from an unslowed XP mob, with a mana consumption rate similar to that from full-bore DD casting. You wouldn't be able to cast anything else, but you would be able to "park" the mob as long as you had mana. Allows for "off-tanking" (with an appropriate overall damage penalty) as well as holding up a pet long enough against adds to let your party and/or you to escape.
<br />

<br />
At 35 mana/sec consumption (same as chaining SV) less 10 mana/sec regen (horse, FT15, buffs) you would plow through 5000 mana in about 200 seconds. At 100 DPS on a potential pet, that is a 20kHP mob. Add 500 seconds to regen the 5000 mana, you are looking at around 12 min/kill-cycle. That doesn't seem overpowering to me.
<br />

<br />
Right now, it is that we can do that against very low 50s mobs, not quite "XP mobs" for a level 65 player of any gear/AA/experience level.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
