<br />

<br />
Based on the way pets take damage, I don't think that 1200 and 2000 would be an appropriate fix.
<br />

<br />
Like I hinted at above, we need to establish a fair baseline for existing pets and abilities, but then allow room for growth based on AA's and the pet focii that rytan spoke of in the other forum. I think the numbers I threw out in the original idea represent a fair starting point. The other possibility would be to have them start a little bit lower, but scale upwards to level 65. As an example, TER could heal for 2500 hp at level 60, but heal for 3000 at level 65. PR could heal for 3500 at level 64, and then heal for 4000 at level 65. I believe that healing spells can scale based on the level of the caster, much like DD spells can.
<br />

<br />
From there, we may need a healing AA, ancient type healing spell, or healing focus items to help our heals scale with the new focii.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1002541&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
