				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like the % idea, but have they ever really done this before with a healing or damage effect?   Would the % heal be calculated based on the base hit points of the pet, or the buffed hitpoints? 
<br />

<br />
Remember, in a raid situation, some pets will qualify for /mgb buffs, and will have quite a few more hp than we are used to seeing. That being said, going with a % would certainly cover the issue of having the heal scale with buffs and some of the improved foci.
<br />

<br />
The drawback to a % heal, is that it can be considered overpowered. If the 52 heal will heal 50% of a pets hitpoints, that means it will do so in future expansions as well, cutting down on a possible area of advancement within the class.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1002541&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
